### GroupsApp — API Test File
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000/api
### Use the REST Client extension in VS Code (humao.rest-client)

@base = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = REPLACE_WITH_JWT_TOKEN

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### AUTH
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### Register a new user
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

###

### Register a second user
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

###

### Login
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### USERS
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### Search users by username
GET {{base}}/users/search?q=bob
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get user by ID
GET {{base}}/users/REPLACE_WITH_USER_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### GROUPS
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### Create a group
POST {{base}}/groups
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Proyecto Telemática",
  "description": "Grupo del proyecto distribuido"
}

###

### List my groups
GET {{base}}/groups
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get group by ID
GET {{base}}/groups/REPLACE_WITH_GROUP_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Add member to group (admin only)
POST {{base}}/groups/REPLACE_WITH_GROUP_ID/members
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "userId": "REPLACE_WITH_USER_ID"
}

###

### Remove member from group (admin only)
DELETE {{base}}/groups/REPLACE_WITH_GROUP_ID/members/REPLACE_WITH_USER_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### CHANNELS
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### Create a channel in a group
POST {{base}}/groups/REPLACE_WITH_GROUP_ID/channels
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "general",
  "description": "Canal principal del grupo"
}

###

### List channels of a group
GET {{base}}/groups/REPLACE_WITH_GROUP_ID/channels
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### MESSAGES
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### Get messages from a group (paginated)
GET {{base}}/messages/REPLACE_WITH_GROUP_ID?type=group&limit=50&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get messages from a channel
GET {{base}}/messages/REPLACE_WITH_CHANNEL_ID?type=channel&limit=50&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get DM messages between two users
GET {{base}}/messages/REPLACE_WITH_OTHER_USER_ID?type=dm&limit=50&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Mark all messages in a target as read
POST {{base}}/messages/REPLACE_WITH_TARGET_ID/read?type=group
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### FILES
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### Upload a file to S3
POST {{base}}/files/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="image.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./test-image.png
------FormBoundary--

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### WEBSOCKET EVENTS (reference)
### ─────────────────────────────────────
# Connect with: io('http://localhost:3000', { auth: { token: 'YOUR_JWT' } })
#
# Client → Server:
#   join:group     { groupId }
#   leave:group    { groupId }
#   join:channel   { channelId }
#   leave:channel  { channelId }
#   send:message   { targetId, targetType: 'group'|'channel'|'dm', content, fileUrl? }
#   typing:start   { targetId, targetType }
#   typing:stop    { targetId, targetType }
#   read:messages  { targetId, targetType }
#
# Server → Client:
#   message:new     { message }
#   message:read    { targetId, readBy, readAt }
#   presence:update { userId, status: 'online'|'offline' }
#   typing:update   { userId, targetId, isTyping }
